eating.\nUse energy saving shower heads and flow controls which provide only the necessary amount of water for the job. This in particular can have substantial effects of reducing CO2 emissions of a house that heats with fossil fuels and is very easy and quite cheap to implement (about \u00a335 in my case).\nHaving done the above reduced my emissions at home by about 1000kg per year and even though I live in a residence that has fossil fuel heating where the average emissions per person are about to 2230kg annually, I have now lowered my portion to under 900kg CO2 annually for heat and water, the rest of the necessary heat is generated by resistive heaters with renewable energy since it is not possible for me to install a heat pump here.", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "124316213", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124316863", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1546767086000}, "author": "ohcomeoffit", "author_id": "3037029", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "> I'm amazed that we are still having to have this conversation\nNo offence: we aren't having to. The notion that we are is just one more blunt weapon, in the arsenal of sophistry used by denialists and excuse-pedlars. They raise doubts they don't harbour and pretend to defend claims they don't believe, with logic they know is flawed. Nobody's stupid enough to be convinced by them and they know that too. Their intent isn't persuasion, it's distraction and delay. \"Having this conversation\" with them serves no other purpose. The idea that we have to have it is manufactured as cynically as the conversations themselves.", "recommendation_count": "18", "in_reply_to": "124315861", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124316840", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1546767032000}, "author": "Steve Jones", "author_id": "11108528", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Nonsense.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "124316300", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124316815", "tim