 similar cost to fossil fuels.\nWhat I am doing now is not going to fix anything. But it will make things worse more slowly - giving us just a fraction more time. I believe the trick is to subsidise and invest in new construction, with increased cost only coming from actual generation. Then when the technology ages, construction of replacement technology will be much more economically viable.", "recommendation_count": "7", "in_reply_to": "124890155", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "i limit the distance i drive", "effect": "yet i burn about as much petrol as the average prius driver"}]}, {"id": "124890680", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548004361000}, "author": "Birkenhead90210", "author_id": "16541072", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nOR, we can get some sort of people's car built,\nBQEND\nHmm, I think we might need to work on that name... it has some rather unfortunate historical connotations...", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "124890087", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124890645", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548004306000}, "author": "wardpj", "author_id": "4096579", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Capitalism!is may have developed in the way you describe in the last thirty years, but your diagnosis doesn't explain what nothing was done when climate change forst became a major public issue 1988, as the article points out).", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "124890165", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124890623", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548004264000}, "author": "twitgit", "author_id": "16045352", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "So, so, right. What government minister, Clark (BEIS), Grayling (Transport hahaha), Gove (Agriculture) is going to say to the electorate: stop driving, stop flying, stop taking holidays abroad, stop eating meat? And that all needs to happen across the World. Basically humanity is f****d.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "1