er open fires. Someone even walked an elephant across the river by Blackfriars Bridge.\nThey could not have known, as the climate warmed and the river was cleaned up, that this would the last time they would ever indulge in such hedonistic but no doubt highly enjoyable pastimes.", "keyword_urls": ["https://www.theguardian.com/uk/london", "https://www.theguardian.com/environment/climate-change", "https://www.theguardian.com/tone/features"], "share_count": "0", "description": "The winter of 1813/14 was one of the coldest on record, and Londoners played, drank, danced and enjoyed themselves on the frozen Thames", "date_published": {"$date": 1548451846000}, "date_modified": {"$date": 1548451846000}, "authors": ["Stephen Moss"], "article_section": "News", "article_tags": ["Winter", "London", "UK news", "Climate change"], "og_fields": {"og:url": "http://www.theguardian.com/news/2019/jan/25/weatherwatch-last-thames-frost-fair", "og:description": "The winter of 1813/14 was one of the coldest on record, and Londoners played, drank, danced and enjoyed themselves on the frozen Thames", "og:image": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/94106456e0a60abab6d40da5440e5ab19f36971d/118_493_4809_2884/master/4809.jpg?width=1200&height=630&quality=85&auto=format&fit=crop&overlay-align=bottom%2Cleft&overlay-width=100p&overlay-base64=L2ltZy9zdGF0aWMvb3ZlcmxheXMvdGctZGVmYXVsdC5wbmc&s=d2910f523cd710ebcb3cd3e6e9d343e8", "og:type": "article", "og:title": "Weatherwatch: a good time had by all at the last Thames frost fair"}, "discussion_section_open": false, "headline": "l", "article_image": [{"type": "http://schema.org/ImageObject", "properties": {"representativeOfPage": "true", "url": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/94106456e0a60abab6d40da5440e5ab19f36971d/52_30_4981_3341/master/4981.jpg?width=700&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=04092f733ae391d7a5709338e873ec58", "width": "4981", "height": "3341", "contentUrl": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/94106456e0a60abab6d40da5440e5ab19f36971d/52_30_4981_33