h out of the repeated cycle of glacials and interglacials that has been going on for a couple of million years.\nThe huge rise in CO2 since the start of the Industrial Revolution has certainly reversed a long-term cooling trend.\nThe warmest part of this interglacial ran from about 9000 years ago until about 5000 years ago, and temperatures varied a little during this time, with some ups and downs. This phase is called the Mid-Holocene Climatic Optimum.\nIt might have been (just about) as warm as in the later 20th century, but only in the summer and only in the northern hemisphere.\nThe long-term cooling trend began around 5000 years ago, after the Mid-Holocene Climatic Optimum.", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "125187095", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125218267", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548764951000}, "author": "dontscamme", "author_id": "12231106", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nIt's in their interests to scare people as much as possible.\nBQENDHow are people going to force governments to act unless as many people as possible get scared?", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125168889", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125218108", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548764808000}, "author": "dontscamme", "author_id": "12231106", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nIf no one sold generators after hurricane Katrina, more people would have suffered.\nBQENDFar less would have suffered if Bush had bothered to send Federal generators.\nIf no one sold extortionately priced black market food during any famine you might name, more people would have suffered, but making ludicrous profits from watching people die, well, that's just business.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125164097", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125202758", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548735006000}, "author": "minotaur", "author_id": "2108985", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I'm n