of our large black coal fired power stations. Large utility scale concentrations of photovoltaic panels such as are being rolled out in Queensland and large scale wind farms such as as being built in southern Australia and North Queensland require no more additional grid upgrade than a coal, gas or nuclear plant of similar capacity.\nAustralia is a major exporter of uranium with the world's largest uranium mine in South Australia. A inquiry into the nuclear industry options possible for that state found that, at least for the next two decades, a nuclear power plant to supply power to the 1.7 million South Australians was uneconomic. There has been no similar inquiry into the economics of nuclear power for Victoria (population 6.4 million), New South Wales (population 7.4 million) or Queensland (population 5 million). The cost of producing electricity from nuclear power stations even in countries with large concentrated populations is greater than the renewable and gas alternatives in Australia. Unlike gas turbines and hydro nuclear and coal fired plants have problems with quick dispatchability.", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "125389031", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "airconditioner use", "effect": "peak demand"}]}, {"id": "125381334", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1549039620000}, "author": "ComfortablyPlumb", "author_id": "14842422", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "okay, just wanted to make the distinction.Thanks.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125377728", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125380349", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1549038083000}, "author": "RJander", "author_id": "15758543", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "And it has to happen quickly starting now, not Dec 31, 2049.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "125342667", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125394294", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1549089882000}, "author": "Mazter", "author_id": "11150889", "schema_org_type": "http: