 saying, all human intervention has it's 'downsides' and assuming that relatively frequent cold burns, even 'patchwork' ones, is an 'answer' to catastrophic wildfires is probably optimistic, if not simplistic. Plants need to exceed reproductive maturity in order to replenish soil-born seed banks - which are vital, as I'm sure you also know.\nI worry when I hear people who just want more and more 'burning off' as a panacea to 'protect' property start quoting indigenous practices - particularly reactionaries who have agendas that don't include botanical diversity . Forests are more than the trees, and even trees who have 'resprouting' as their regeneration after fire strategy can be depleted beyond their ability. Especially in a climate constrained ecosystem.\nCheers, and thanks for pointing me in the direction of button grass plains... shall have to investigate.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125311441", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125335017", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548936487000}, "author": "walker1", "author_id": "4151007", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Hang in there Doggy a lot of people are behind you and caring for you and those you love.", "recommendation_count": "1", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125333348", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548934338000}, "author": "Heckle", "author_id": "3166235", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "yeah, imagine if the Defence Force actually did some defending for a change, instead of attacking overseas third world countries in religious crusades", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "125291860", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125330269", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548930877000}, "author": "MorvaHindrance", "author_id": "16761029", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I just had a look at the BOM interactive weather forecast for Tasmania and for the first time ever it is forecasting smoke. Liawenee will be zero overnight with s