 remain going strong just so that we we have the money to convert all these industrial plants and so on away from fossil fuels. If we are poor, then we will never be able to do this. So its that balance between maintaining a functional economy just until we have all industry, heating etc decarbonised and switched to hydrogen. \nBoth CCS and electrolysis will be used in order to decarbonise our gas grids; but the low cost of renewable electricity (and electrolysers) and the use of hydrogen in transport (and fuel cells for heating etc) should necessitate generic use of hydrogen only. The risk of using methane, or continuing its use, is too high.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "124943277", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "we may not have the money in the future to make the fundamental changes necessary", "effect": "we should spend money on what we genuinely need to do now"}]}, {"id": "124950779", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548138181000}, "author": "rockyrex", "author_id": "2923581", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Jaguar Land Rover built their UK engine plant not far from here a few years ago - they are now going to start building Electric Drive Units there.\nThe roof of this very large factory is covered with more than 21,000 photovoltaic panels, with a capacity of 5.8MW.\nIndustry knows that non-fossil energy is fast becoming the cheapest option.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "124944487", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124949986", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548131708000}, "author": "thebowsie", "author_id": "2484923", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nLomborg's \"The Skeptical Environmentalist\" is a truly thought-provoking manifesto.\nBQEND\nNot according to his national ethics watchdog, The Danish Committee for Scientific Dishonesty. Here's what they had to say about the book:\n\"[T]he publication is deemed clearly contrary to the standards of good scientific practice... there ha