ing sea-levels under the Liberals.\nIt is very similar to when Malcolm Turnbull said that if one wanted to address climate, a market-based mechanism (such as carbon pricing) would be the best way... then the Liberal Party fought tooth-and-nail to prevent any such pricing mechanism, and indeed overturned an existing/working one (introduced by Gillard). In the same way, the NSW Liberal Party knew the right path to plan for rising sea-levels, then overturned their own law on the matter, to allow/encourage climate-denialism.\nI'm sure there's a lesson there somewhere!", "recommendation_count": "19", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124754751", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1547683108000}, "author": "Panjandrum1", "author_id": "4364000", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "The most amazing thing about the beach at Collaroy-Narrabeen is there are still people who think buildings backing onto it can be saved. Streets have been washed away in the past. There were expectations of buildings being washed away in the 1960s. Every few years more are put in danger. It is just not possible to save them over the long term. Sorry Wendy, but public money should not be spent on trying to save private homes built where they should never have been built.", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "124733018", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124756791", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1547690058000}, "author": "djw300", "author_id": "2947349", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I bought my mountain home in Melbourne's east with a long term plan of buying a boat and mooring it in the backyard.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "124755369", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124756788", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1547690048000}, "author": "Nigel Evans", "author_id": "18426188", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Whoosh.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "124754500", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "124754744"