ople can kill an animal how can people kill plants with the new data coming out that shows that plant life experiences pain. -New research on plant intelligence may forever change how you think about plants:Michael Pollan, author of such books as \"The Omnivore's Dilemma\" and \"The Botany of Desire,\" stated new research, he says, is in a field called plant neurobiology.\"They have analagous structures,\" Pollan explains. \"They (plants) have ways of taking all the sensory data they gather in their everyday lives ... integrate it and then behave in an appropriate way in response. And they do this without brains, which, in a way, is what's incredible about it, because we automatically assume you need a brain to process information.\" \nPlants don't have similar nervous systems as animals but they have something that is equal to animal intelligence. An example: Pollan, played a recording of a caterpillar munching on a leaf to plants \u2014 and the plants react. They begin to secrete defensive chemicals \u2014 even though the plant isn't really threatened, Pollan says. \"It is somehow hearing what is, to it, a terrifying sound of a caterpillar munching on its leaves.\" Another observation is when a plant is being eaten by an insect the plants next to it will actually began to lean away from the attacked plant which some researchers say is a fear reaction. Lots of research over the last decade on plant life intelligence. Just because you can't hear them scream doesn't mean they don't feel pain when they are chopped up or yanked from the ground. \nMy point. Stop judging other people. You don't want to eat meat that's fine-do your thang but stop thinking that make you a better person than those who do chose to eat meat. Your lifestyle choice contributes to climate change more than you want to believe if you read scientific articles that are based on studies & testing. Just think about all the articles on Halloween pumpkins last year and how they contribute to an increase