ops, clover & rye (green manure) to supplement regular amounts of rotted sheep manure. I use rock dust. I supplement my irrigation with micro nutrients. I apply dolomite year round....my soil is decomposed granite...nearly 100% sand and last year we got 2 000mm of rain (about 80 inches) so my calcium gets leached...and as you probably know, without calcium and zinc you can grow nothing.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125173567", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "you are able to consume them much sooner after they 've been picked", "effect": "the reason why your produce has a much higher mineral and vitamin content is"}, {"cause": "i put a lot of effort into my soil", "effect": "the reason why my produce has a much higher mineral and vitamin content is"}]}, {"id": "125176891", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548685403000}, "author": "minceroll", "author_id": "14670239", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Too right. Bring back the workhouses.(sarcasm, just in case you didn't know)", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "125156316", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125176869", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548685378000}, "author": "c.l. shannon", "author_id": "100151035", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I think they ought to be subsidizing the meat. Kids need protein.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "125165589", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "125176860", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1548685365000}, "author": "JTStone", "author_id": "4300674", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "It's surreal reading these reports and knowing that they're almost certainly right, but that there's nothing much I can do that I'm not already doing. Without some measure of financial stability I simply can't devote time to campaigning, and the impact of campaigning in any case (no disrespect to those who engage with it) is insufficient to change the course. I'm not falling into despair and of course I'l